<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="57.[128,654,211,1759]" lastBlockId="57.[701,1228,213,822]" pageId="57" pageNumber="57">
DISCUSSION: This species is very similar in coloration and size to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menard &amp; Schuh" authorityYear="2011" box="[432,654,1650,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ausejanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[432,654,1650,1671]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="57">Ausejanus minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[286,409,1679,1700]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="57" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Myrtaceae</taxonomicName>
hosts in 
<collectingRegion box="[532,650,1679,1701]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="57" pageNumber="57">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
, females of both species having the anterior margin of the transverse fascia gold. How- ever, the combination of males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menard &amp; Schuh" authorityYear="2011" box="[1099,1169,213,234]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ausejanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iris">
<emphasis box="[1099,1169,213,234]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="57">A. iris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with white pigmentation and the asteraceous host plant (
<emphasis box="[780,911,271,294]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="57">Ozothamnu</emphasis>
s) clearly separate the two. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menard &amp; Schuh" authorityYear="2011" box="[701,918,301,322]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ausejanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arvensus">
<emphasis box="[701,918,301,322]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="57">Ausejanus arvensus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also found on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ozothamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="57" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="57">Ozothamnus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, but neither males nor females have white pigmentation and the hemelytron is paler.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
